headline: Coca-Cola Shifts From Frozen Juices As KO Trades Near Fair Value
summary: Coca-Cola is discontinuing Minute Maid frozen juice concentrates in the U.S. and Canada after nearly 80 years. The company is shifting its juice portfolio toward ready to drink and refrigerated options such as Simply and Fairlife. This move reflects Coca-Cola's focus on convenience and chilled products in its North American beverage lineup.
